        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:41PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 441 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Tower Hill, or 7 miles southwest of Shelbyville, moving southwest at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shelbyville, Cowden, Herrick, Clarksburg, and Lakewood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Conditions are favorable for the development of weak, brief funnel
clouds. This type of funnel cloud is harmless, but on rare occasions
they can briefly touch down, producing wind gusts over 50 mph. If a
funnel cloud is spotted move indoors and report your sighting to the
National Weather Service.</instruction>
